1.77.0 Â· [source](about:blank/src/std/fs.rs.html#437-439)

Creates a new file in read-write mode; error if the file exists.

This function will create a file if it does not exist, or return an error if it does. This way, if the call succeeds, the file returned is guaranteed to be new. If a file exists at the target location, creating a new file will fail with [`AlreadyExists`](about:blank/io/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.AlreadyExists "variant std::io::ErrorKind::AlreadyExists") or another error based on the situation. See [`OpenOptions::open`](about:blank/struct.OpenOptions.html#method.open "method std::fs::OpenOptions::open") for a non-exhaustive list of likely errors.

This option is useful because it is atomic. Otherwise between checking whether a file exists and creating a new one, the file may have been created by another process (a TOCTOU race condition / attack).

This can also be written using `File::options().read(true).write(true).create_new(true).open(...)`.

