Truncates or extends the underlying file, updating the size of this file to become `size`.

If the `size` is less than the current fileâ€™s size, then the file will be shrunk. If it is greater than the current fileâ€™s size, then the file will be extended to `size` and have all of the intermediate data filled in with 0s.

The fileâ€™s cursor isnâ€™t changed. In particular, if the cursor was at the end and the file is shrunk using this operation, the cursor will now be past the end.

